main event: A witness in Cincinnati, Ohio reported seeing a bright red object that then became two white objects in the sky on 15 September 1967.
interesting points: The objects appeared to be round in shape and moved in an erratic, jerky manner, darting from one position to another.
The objects were visible for about 45-60 minutes, but were not continuously in sight.
The witness stated the objects changed color from red to white and their brightness also changed.
The objects were reported to move behind and in front of clouds at times.
The witness estimated the objects were several hundred feet away and made no sound.
sighted object: bright red object that became two white objects
photographs: no photographs included in the report
